Defendant Shelly M Zais in court with attorney Carl William Chesshir.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following:
- 1 year Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED.  Credit for 1 day if revoked.
- 2 years Probation.  Probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County.
- Court costs of $278.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Restitution of $318.12 to be paid (jointly and severally liable) to FIA Card Services as a Condition of Probation
- Conditions of Probation:  No contact with any codefendant.  No contact with victim.  Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs. No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Maintain part-time employment.  DNA Sample if not yet provided, defendant to pay surcharge.
